<body>
    <h1>Algorithm for Data Encryption Standard</h1>
    <p>The Data Encryption Standard (DES) is a symmetric-key algorithm for the encryption of electronic data. It uses a 56-bit key for encryption and decryption. This demo allows you to encrypt a message using DES with a specified number of encryption steps.</p>

    <div id="control-panel">
        <div class="input-group">
            <label for="input-message">message</label>
            <input type="text" id="input-message" value="hello">
        </div>
        <div class="input-group">
            <label for="input-key">key</label>
            <input type="text" id="input-key" value="test">
        </div>
        <div class="input-group">
            <label>steps</label>
            <div class="segmented-control">
                <input type="radio" id="radio-steps-2" name="steps" value="2">
                <label for="radio-steps-2">2</label>
                <input type="radio" id="radio-steps-4" name="steps" value="4">
                <label for="radio-steps-4">4</label>
                <input type="radio" id="radio-steps-8" name="steps" value="8">
                <label for="radio-steps-8">8</label>
                <input type="radio" id="radio-steps-16" name="steps" value="16" checked>
                <label for="radio-steps-16">16</label>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="output-container">
        <div class="header">
            <span id="output-header-permutations">Permutations in Encryption</span>
            <span id="output-header-message">Encrypted Message</span>
        </div>
